{
  "texts": [
    "As one of the major approaches for drug discovery, various methods have been suggested for generating molecules with desired properties [9] [10] [11] 13.",
    "In the approaches presented so far, the maximum number of simultaneously controllable properties wasn't very large.",
    "Also, the length of the input property vector cannot be changed.",
    "Whenever the target properties change, the model needs to be trained again for the new wanted conditions.",
    "In contrast, the pre-trained SPMM can take 53 properties used in pre-training as input conditions and generate molecules that satisfy all of them, without separate additional training for each property combination."
  ]
}